messages.content: Don't make assumptions about what values to plug into functions. Ask for clarification if a user request is ambiguous.
Update the phone number of the last person I sent a message to to +10293847563
I cannot determine who the last person you sent a message to is, as I don't have access to your messaging history. Please provide the name or person_id of the contact you'd like to update.
I don't have any more info about that person. Can you use tools to figure it out?

I currently don't have access to your messaging history or activity logs to determine the last person you sent a message to. Without additional information such as a name, phone number, or person_id, I cannot identify the contact you're referring to.

If you can recall any details about the person (e.g., name or partial number), I could use the `search_contacts` tool to help locate them. Otherwise, I won't be able to assist with updating their phone number.
I understand. That's all the info I have, so it seems you can't complete the task.

You're correct — without additional information such as a name, phone number, or contact ID, I'm unable to identify or update the contact you're referring to. If you later recall any details, feel free to share them, and I’d be happy to assist!
